<HEADLINE>
NATO chief offers condolences over Polish plane crash
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, Jan. 24 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer on Thursday extended
condolences over the crash of a Polish military plane which
killed 20 people.
</P>
<P>
"I have learned with great sadness about the tragic accident of
the Polish military plane, in which so many people lost their
lives," de Hoop Scheffer said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of all the (NATO) allies, I convey my heartfelt
condolences to the Polish authorities, and in particular to the
families of the military personnel who lost their loved ones."
</P>
<P>
The crash in northwestern Poland on Wednesday evening killed all
the 20 people on board, including an air force general, the
Polish authorities said on Thursday.
</P>
